<p><a name="Other_books" id="Other_books"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Muir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Other books">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Other books</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSachs2006">Sachs, Aaron (2006). <i>The Humboldt Current: Nineteenth-Century Exploration and the Roots of American Environmentalism</i>. Viking Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0670037753" class="internal">ISBN 0-670-03775-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Humboldt+Current%3A+Nineteenth-Century+Exploration+and+the+Roots+of+American+Environmentalism&amp;rft.aulast=Sachs&amp;rft.aufirst=Aaron&amp;rft.au=Sachs%2C+Aaron&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pub=Viking+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-670-03775-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:John_Muir"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Muir is one of four people the author focuses on who were influenced by <a href="/wiki/Alexander_von_Humboldt" title="Alexander von Humboldt">Alexander von Humboldt</a>.</li>
</ul>
